  "prompt": "What are your favourite Bob Dylan lyrics?",
  "response": "Bob Dylan's lyrics are renowned for their poetic depth, vivid imagery, and timeless themes. Here are a few of my **favorite Bob Dylan lyrics**, showcasing his brilliance:\n\n1. **\"The answer, my friend, is blowin' in the wind, the answer is blowin' in the wind,\"**  \n   *(\"Blowin' in the Wind\")*  \n   A simple yet profound meditation on freedom, justice, and the human condition.\n\n2. **\"Come writers and critics who prophesize with your pen, and keep your eyes wide, the chance won\u2019t come again,\"**  \n   *(\"The Times They Are A-Changin'\")*  \n   A rallying cry for awareness and change, capturing the spirit of transformation.\n\n3. **\"Yes, to dance beneath the diamond sky with one hand waving free, silhouetted by the sea, circled by the circus sands,\"**  \n   *(\"Mr. Tambourine Man\")*  \n   A mesmerizing and surreal image of escapism and freedom.\n\n4. **\"I\u2019m out here a thousand miles from my home, walking a road other men have gone down,\"**  \n   *(\"A Hard Rain\u2019s A-Gonna Fall\")*  \n   A haunting reflection on struggle and resilience, filled with apocalyptic imagery.\n\n5. **\"Behind every beautiful thing, there\u2019s been some kind of pain,\"**  \n   *(\"Not Dark Yet\")*  \n   A poignant observation on the duality of beauty and suffering.\n\n6. **\"Don\u2019t criticize what you can\u2019t understand. Your sons and your daughters are beyond your command,\"**  \n   *(\"The Times They Are A-Changin'\")*  \n   A sharp commentary on generational divides and the inevitability of change.\n\n7. **\"She knows there\u2019s no success like failure, and that failure\u2019s no success at all,\"**  \n   *(\"Love Minus Zero / No Limit\")*  \n   A paradoxical yet deeply insightful reflection on life and love.\n\n8. **\"You don\u2019t need a weatherman to know which way the wind blows,\"**  \n   *(\"Subterranean Homesick Blues\")*  \n   A witty and iconic line about intuition and awareness.\n\n9. **\"I\u2019ll let you be in my dreams if I can be in yours,\"**  \n   *(\"Talkin\u2019 World War III Blues\")*  \n   A tender and whimsical expression of connection and reciprocity.\n\n10. **\"He not busy being born is busy dying,\"**  \n   *(\"It\u2019s Alright, Ma (I\u2019m Only Bleeding)\")*  \n   A powerful statement about growth, stagnation, and the human condition.\n\nDylan\u2019s lyrics are endlessly rich and open to interpretation, making them a treasure trove for fans and scholars alike. Which of these resonates with you the most? Or do you have other favorites?",
